Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into
2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams} using a #grater{}. In a
large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat, combine the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} along with
their liquid, @Finely Chopped Tomatoes with Onion and Garlic{1/2%carton}, @Red Wine
Stock Paste{28%grams}, @Chipotle Paste{20%grams} and the @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp}.

> Add less chipotle paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Bring the chipotle chilli to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly
thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once the chilli has thickened, stir in the @butter{20%grams} until melted. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the potato wedges between your #serving bowls{}. Top with the mixed bean chipotle
chilli.

Drizzle over the @Soured Cream{75%grams} and sprinkle over the cheese to finish.

Enjoy!